results.name: Number of ordered quadruples of distinct pairwise coprime positive integers with largest element n; also first differences of A015623.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
example: a(4) = 0 because there is only one ordered quadruple of distinct positive integers with largest element 4, (1,2,3,4), but the elements are not pairwise coprime, 2 and 4 have a common factor >1.
a(8) = 4 because there are only four ordered quadruples of distinct pairwise coprime positive integers with largest element 8: (1,3,5,8), (1,3,7,8), (1,5,7,8), (3,5,7,8).
xref: Cf. A015623, A185953. Column 4 of triangle A186972.
results.author: _Alois P. Heinz_, Feb 15 2011
